Remove-from-list is now snappy. All "Remove from list" gestures (right-click main tree, List menu, Execute Action accept, singleton prune) use an incremental tree update via the new `TreeController.remove_rows` method instead of rebuilding the entire `QStandardItemModel` — ~170k QStandardItem allocations per remove on a 13k-row manifest are now avoided. Selection and expanded-group state survive the remove (#634, closes #630).
